          how: "Range sharding: shard 1 = user_id 1-1M, shard 2 = 1M-2M. Simple but hot shards (new users on last shard). Hash sharding: shard = hash(user_id) % N. Even distribution but range queries hit all shards. Directory: lookup table maps key → shard. Flexible but lookup is bottleneck.",
