          interview: "Common question: 'How would you shard a user database?' Answer: hash on user_id for even distribution. 'How do you rebalance when you add shards?' — consistent hashing minimizes data movement. 'What's the hot shard problem?' — celebrity writes all hit same shard (hash of celebrity_id). Fix: split hot shard or use separate celebrity table.",
          example: "Discord shards Cassandra by guild_id — all messages for a server on one shard, enabling efficient range scans. Instagram sharded PostgreSQL with user_id % 512 → 512 logical shards on 32 physical servers (16 shards/server). Resharding: dual-write to old + new shard → verify → cutover.",
