          interview: "Draw the ring. Explain: 'When node D joins between B and C, only the keys between B and D move — about 1/N of total keys.' Virtual nodes question: 'Without virtual nodes, if hash(node1) and hash(node2) are close together, node2 handles almost all traffic.' Used by: Cassandra, AWS DynamoDB, Akamai CDN.",
          example: "Cassandra adds a new node to a 3-node cluster: consistent hashing moves exactly 1/4 of the key range to the new node (25%), not 75% as modulo hashing would. Amazon ElastiCache uses consistent hashing for Memcached — adding one node only remaps ~1/N of cached keys, not the full cache.",
