          interview: "Pair with Event Sourcing: 'Write side stores events; read side projects events into views.' Simple example: Instagram post counts — writes go to normalized Posts table, read model maintains denormalized counts in Redis updated via events. Say: 'CQRS lets us use Redis for reads and Postgres for writes, each optimized for their purpose.'",
          example: "Zalando order service: write model (Postgres, normalized order tables) publishes OrderCreated events → read model (Elasticsearch) indexes denormalized order views for search/filtering. Read latency went from 200ms (Postgres joins) to 5ms (Elasticsearch). Write volume: 50K orders/day; read volume: 10M searches/day.",
