          example: "DynamoDB (AP): during a network partition, DynamoDB continues accepting writes from both sides → conflict resolved by last-write-wins. Shopping carts can diverge → merge on read. HBase (CP): during partition, HBase returns errors to minority partition rather than serve stale data — correct for financial/inventory use cases where wrong data is worse than no data.",
